  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Input finance arrangement for the sesame sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Creating access to finance is one of the agriterra goals aspired to be achieved before 2020. In certain sectors, like the sesame sector, input finance for farmers is crucial in order to acquire seeds, fertilizers, labor or other related inputs. As it is often very challenging to get access to input finance, Agriterra would like to execute two input finance pilots, with the aim of providing farmers better access to input finance. This will be carried out together with a cooperative bank Oromia in Ethiopia.

Agriterra plays a pivotal role of not only in strengthening cooperatives, but also by creating access to finance from financial institutions such as CBO/Cooperative bank of Oromia, by narrowing down the &#x2018;collateral gap&#x2019; that exists between cooperatives and the bank. This way, Agriterra approached the CBO to release 4 million ETB for two Unions; 4 Primary cooperatives, benefiting about 2000 smallholders. A unique guarantee arrangement is discussed with CBO on partaking proportionate risk to release the required sum, details of the arrangement stated is in a separate proposal.

- 2016: resolving the double registration of SOPACDI and assure audits done and presented to AGM for 2013, 2014 and 2015 - This is a condition for further actions in 2017 focussed on marketing, internal capitalisation, etc.</narrative>
  </description>
